The paper discusses distributed estimation over adaptive networks, which involves the interaction and diffusion of information between nodes. This topic is closely related to the field of multi-agent systems and networked control, which falls under the cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) sub-category. The paper also analyzes the mean-square performance of different strategies for distributed estimation, which involves information theory and signal processing concepts, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the stability and convergence properties of the networks, which are important topics in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper uses simulation results to support the theoretical findings, which is a common approach in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
